<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10603225>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Oliarus pinicolus Osborn, 1926 (male; A, B, D, E lectotype, C paralectotype); A) habitus, dorsal view; B), same, lateral view; C) head, frontal view; D) head and thorax; E) labels." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10603225/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10603227>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Aedeagal complex of Oliarus pinicolus; A) aedeagal complex (ventral), annotated B) aedeagal complex, ventral view; C) same, dorsal view; D) ventral view of external male terminalia before dissection; E) aedeagal complex (left lateral); F) aedeagal complex (right lateral); annotations: Dp = dextral process of ventral periandrium, Es = endosoma, EsA = apical process of endosoma, EsD = dorsal subapical process of endosoma, EsV = ventral subapical process of endosoma, Mdp = mediodorsal process of periandrium, Mvp = medioventral process of periandrium, Sp = sinistral process of ventral periandrium." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10603227/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10603231>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Oliarus pinicolus terminalia (in glycerin); A) male terminalia before disarticulation; B) aedeagal complex, ventral view; C) same, dorsal view; D) anal tube, right lateral view; E) left gonostyle; F) anal tube, dorsal view; G) aedeagal complex, left lateral view; H) same, right lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10603231/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10603233>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Forewing venation of Oliarus pinicolus; black text – veins, italics – crossveins, green text – cells, abbreviations following Bourgoin et al. (2015)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10603233/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

